#### Wei-Lin-Weissfeld model

For the Wei-Lin-Weissfeld model you must specify:

-   `formula = Surv(stop, event) ~ 'predictors' + strata(enum)`

-   `cluster = id`

And the data structure must be:

| Id  | Time interval | Start | Stop | Event | Enum |
|-----|---------------|-------|------|-------|------|
| 1   | (0, 1\]       | 0     | 1    | 0     | 1    |
| 1   | (0, 1\]       | 0     | 1    | 0     | 2    |
| 1   | (0, 1\]       | 0     | 1    | 0     | 3    |
| 1   | (0, 1\]       | 0     | 1    | 0     | 4    |
| 2   | (0, 4\]       | 0     | 4    | 0     | 1    |
| 2   | (0, 4\]       | 0     | 4    | 0     | 2    |
| 2   | (0, 4\]       | 0     | 4    | 0     | 3    |
| 2   | (0, 4\]       | 0     | 4    | 0     | 4    |
| 3   | (0, 7\]       | 0     | 7    | 0     | 1    |
| 3   | (0, 7\]       | 0     | 7    | 0     | 2    |
| 3   | (0, 7\]       | 0     | 7    | 0     | 3    |
| 3   | (0, 7\]       | 0     | 7    | 0     | 4    |
| 4   | (0, 10\]      | 0     | 10   | 0     | 1    |
| 4   | (0, 10\]      | 0     | 10   | 0     | 2    |
| 4   | (0, 10\]      | 0     | 10   | 0     | 3    |
| 4   | (0, 10\]      | 0     | 10   | 0     | 4    |
| 5   | (0, 6\]       | 0     | 6    | 1     | 1    |
| 5   | (0, 10\]      | 0     | 10   | 0     | 2    |
| 5   | (0, 10\]      | 0     | 10   | 0     | 3    |
| 5   | (0, 10\]      | 0     | 10   | 0     | 4    |

We will use the `bladder` data for this.



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
WLW <- coxph(Surv(stop, event) ~ as.factor(rx) + number + size + strata(enum),
            ties = "breslow",
            cluster = id,
            data = bladder)
summary(WLW)
```

